(sv)
The Residents tolkar Elvis.
Om det inte vore f&ouml;r texterna skulle det
vara praktiskt taget om&ouml;jligt att h&ouml;ra n&aring;gra
som helst kopplingar till Elvis Presley.

Fast &aring; andra sidan p&aring;minnde Elvis version av
"Hound Dog" inte mycket mer om Big Mama Thorntons
originalversion &auml;n vad Residents version
p&aring;minner om Presleys.

I vilket fall som helst s&aring; b&ouml;r Elvis-fans h&aring;lla sig
borta fr&aring;n denna skiva.

"Jailhouse rock" finns egentligen INTE med p&aring; denna skiva,
men jag har sl&auml;ngt in den som en bonus.


(eng)
The Residents interpret Elvis.
If it weren't for the lyrics, it would be
impossible to hear that any of these songs
are even remotely related to Elvis Presley.

But on the other hand, Elvis' version of
"Hound Dog" doesn't sound much more like
the Big Mama Thornton original than the
Residential version sound like Presley's.

But no matter what, Elvis fans should not be
exposed to this album.

"Jailhouse rock" did NOT appear on this album,
but I've trown it in as a bonus.
